  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The corresponding lattice calculations are performed on N τ = 12 lattices and with limited statistics.",
    "Another lattice study that also uses N τ = 12 lattices, but with much larger statistics, extracted a different result [109].",
    "Here, simple but physically motivated parametrizations of the spectral functions were used to obtain the real and imaginary parts of the potential: the real part of the potential turns out not to be screened in general [109].",
    "The only way to obtain a screened potential from the lattice results of Ref.",
    "[109] is to use a perturbative HTL inspired representation of the spectral function [109]."
  ],
